0:{"rsc":["$","$1","c",{"children":[["$","article",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__articlePage","children":[["$","script",null,{"type":"application/ld+json","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"BlogPosting\",\"headline\":\"Outdoor Kitchen ROI: Is a Built-In Grill Worth it?\",\"image\":[\"https://www.ldndecks.com/images/img11.jpeg\"],\"datePublished\":\"2026-04-21T04:00:00.000Z\",\"dateModified\":\"2026-04-21T04:00:00.000Z\",\"author\":[{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"Nick - Loudoun Decks\",\"url\":\"https://www.ldndecks.com\"}],\"publisher\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"Loudoun Decks\",\"url\":\"https://www.ldndecks.com\",\"logo\":{\"@type\":\"ImageObject\",\"url\":\"https://www.ldndecks.com/ldndecks-logo.webp\"}},\"description\":\"Analyzing the equity gain and lifestyle benefits of professional outdoor culinary spaces. Is a built-in kitchen worth the $15k+ investment?\",\"mainEntityOfPage\":{\"@type\":\"WebPage\",\"@id\":\"https://www.ldndecks.com/blog/outdoor-kitchen-roi-built-in-grill\"},\"isAccessibleForFree\":true,\"inLanguage\":\"en-US\",\"speakable\":{\"@type\":\"SpeakableSpecification\",\"cssSelector\":[\".leadParagraph\",\"h1\",\"h2\"]}}"}}],["$","div",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__heroSection","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__imgWrapper","children":[["$","$L2",null,{"src":"/images/img11.jpeg","alt":"Outdoor Kitchen ROI: Is a Built-In Grill Worth it?","fill":true,"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__heroImg","priority":true,"sizes":"100vw"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__imgOverlay","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__containerLarge","children":[["$","$L3",null,{"href":"/blog","className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__backLink","children":"← Back to News"}],["$","h1",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__title","children":"Outdoor Kitchen ROI: Is a Built-In Grill Worth it?"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__meta","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__author","children":["By ","Nick - Loudoun Decks"]}],["$","span",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__divider","children":"•"}],["$","span",null,{"children":"April 21, 2026"}]]}]]}]}]]}]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__contentSection","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__containerNarrow","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__contentBody","children":[["$","p",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__leadParagraph","children":"Analyzing the equity gain and lifestyle benefits of professional outdoor culinary spaces. Is a built-in kitchen worth the $15k+ investment?"}],[["$","p","0",{"children":"The most requested upgrade for our 2026 deck commissions is the integrated outdoor kitchen. It’s a massive investment—often ranging from $15,000 to $40,000—but does it actually add value to your Northern Virginia home? To answer that, we have to look beyond just the sticker price and analyze the \"equity of lifestyle.\""}],["$","h2","1",{"style":{"marginTop":"40px","marginBottom":"20px","color":"#111"},"children":"The Real Estate Appraisal Perspective"}],["$","p","2",{"children":"In affluent markets like Great Falls and McLean, high-end outdoor kitchens are now an expected amenity for luxury properties. Appraisers typically view a built-in stone kitchen as a permanent architectural improvement, similar to a finished basement. On average, a well-executed outdoor kitchen can recover 60-80% of its initial cost during a home appraisal."}],["$","h2","3",{"style":{"marginTop":"40px","marginBottom":"20px","color":"#111"},"children":"The Lifestyle Dividend"}],["$","p","4",{"children":"The real \"ROI\" comes from how you use your home. By moving the heat and mess of cooking outdoors, you effectively double your entertaining capacity. Modern outdoor kitchens feature:"}],"$L4","$L5","$L6"],"$L7"]}]}]}],"$L8"]}],["$L9"],"$La"]}],"isPartial":false,"staleTime":300,"varyParams":null,"buildId":"Jebrcr4Vyd2YosxlccnHN"}
4:["$","p","5",{"children":"- **Professional Searing Stations:** Capable of reaching 900 degrees for steakhouse-quality results.\n- **Built-in Refrigeration:** No more running back and forth to the kitchen for cold drinks.\n- **Integrated Trash Pullouts:** Keeping your deck clean and hygienic during summer parties."}]
5:["$","h2","6",{"style":{"marginTop":"40px","marginBottom":"20px","color":"#111"},"children":"Structural and Utility Costs"}]
6:["$","p","7",{"children":"When budgeting, remember that the cost isn’t just the appliances. You must factor in running natural gas lines, outdoor-rated electrical circuits, and the structural reinforcement of the deck boards to handle the weight of heavy stone veneer. While the upfront cost is significant, the enjoyment of cooking under the stars with your family is priceless."}]
7:["$","div",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__conclusionBox","children":[["$","h3",null,{"children":"Ready to upgrade your outdoor living space?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Contact Loudoun Decks today for a free estimate and planning consultation."}],["$","$L3",null,{"href":"/contact","className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__ctaBtn","children":"Get Started"}]]}]
